abstract: The scholar, Michael Pillsbury, said the move seemed to be in retaliation for American restrictions on visas for visiting Chinese scholars.
snippet: The scholar, Michael Pillsbury, said the move seemed to be in retaliation for American restrictions on visas for visiting Chinese scholars.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — An American scholar who has advised President Trump on China said late Wednesday that he was not given a visa he sought to attend a recent conference in Beijing, in what he called apparent retaliation for American restrictions on visas for visiting Chinese scholars.

abstract: A little Hitchcock, a touch of noir, some ’90s indie rock, a few naked women, and yet not much to see.
snippet: A little Hitchcock, a touch of noir, some ’90s indie rock, a few naked women, and yet not much to see.
lead_paragraph: Sam is 33 years old, unemployed and counting down the days to eviction from his apartment near the Los Angeles reservoir that gives “Under the Silver Lake” its name. He doesn’t seem too upset about his situation, though he is kind of a mopey guy. His malaise looks like more of a temperamental or existential condition than the response to a crisis. And he doesn’t have it all that bad.

abstract: Concern about mass shootings has lifted spending on studies and attracted a new generation of researchers.
snippet: Concern about mass shootings has lifted spending on studies and attracted a new generation of researchers.
lead_paragraph: In 1996, the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention stopped funding research into the causes of gun violence. And for decades the field suffered from neglect: low funding and a corresponding limited interest in academia.

headline_print_headline: After Years of Poor Funding,  Gun Research Is Suddenly Hot

abstract: While his predecessors sought to broaden their public support, President Trump appears to be heading into his re-election campaign sticking with his own tribe.
snippet: While his predecessors sought to broaden their public support, President Trump appears to be heading into his re-election campaign sticking with his own tribe.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In the last couple of weeks, President Trump repeatedly called his enemies “treasonous.” He threatened to punish Democrats by dumping migrants in their districts. He promoted a video tying a Muslim congresswoman to images of the Sept. 11 terrorist attack on the World Trade Center.

abstract: The confident, elegant composer Huang Ruo might consider expanding his 45-minute chamber opera “Bound.”
snippet: The confident, elegant composer Huang Ruo might consider expanding his 45-minute chamber opera “Bound.”
lead_paragraph: When a new opera has a promising but not entirely successful first performance, its length is often the main problem. Too long, I mean.

abstract: Bernie Sanders is the money leader. Elizabeth Warren is spending big. Pete Buttigieg emerged out of nowhere. And (almost) everyone is buying gobs of Facebook ads.
snippet: Bernie Sanders is the money leader. Elizabeth Warren is spending big. Pete Buttigieg emerged out of nowhere. And (almost) everyone is buying gobs of Facebook ads.
lead_paragraph: The Democratic challengers to President Trump raised tens of millions of dollars in the first months of the 2020 presidential campaign, with Senator Bernie Sanders setting the pace for the field, with $18.2 million raised.
